In practice, this insight suggests a two-step procedure. In the first step, we aim to learn the low-dimensional manifold {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0181||FO}} from {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0182||FO}}, and in the second step, we estimate the mutual information between {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0183||FO}} and {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0184||FO}} from the distances on the learned manifold {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0185||FO}}. In the next section, we propose such an approach based on Geodesic Forests.